WebDriver IO only provides assertions related to the browser or UI controls to get
additional assertions, we need chai package.Which can be installed using 'npm install chai'

WebDriverIO confuses the chai expect with its own expect. To prevent this, import the chai 
package at the beginning of the file.
  const expectChai=require('chai').expect
  expectChai(await dropDown.getValue()).toBe.equal("stud")

Node js is the base js engine where webDriverIO tests will run.Node.js provides a 
runtime environment outside of the browser. It's also built on the Chrome V8 
JavaScript engine. This makes it possible to build back-end applications using the 
same JavaScript programming language you may be familiar with.

#HANDLING DYNAMIC DROPDOWNS
elements appear as you type and then you select the item you want.
 it("Dynamic Dropdown",async()=>{
            await browser.url("https://rahulshettyacademy.com/AutomationPractice/");
            await $("#autocomplete").setValue("ind")
            await browser.pause(2000)
            //selects all items using a common class
            let items=await $$(".ui-menu-item div")
            for(var i=0;i<items.length;i++)
            {
                if(await items[i].getText() === "India")
                {
                    await items[i].click()
                    await browser.pause(2000)
                }
            }
        })

#HANDLING CHECKBOXES
find a common attribute for all options, use $$ to get all options. Access a specific option
and click it.
it("Checkbox handling",async()=>{
            await browser.url("https://rahulshettyacademy.com/AutomationPractice/");
            //since we do not have a common attribute,we use type
            const ele=await $$("input[type='checkbox']")
            await ele[1].click()
            await browser.pause(2000)
            console.log(await ele[1].isSelected())//true
            console.log(await ele[2].isSelected())//false
        })

#TAKING SS OF PAGE
when testcase fails and you don't have a clue why, you take a ss to see how is page behaving
